#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn35.94"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.94:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: 10. Saḷavagga → chaḷavaggo (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "sn35.94:0.2"
msgid "10. Saḷavagga "
msgstr "10. The Sixes "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 94. Adantaaguttasutta → saṃgayha 1 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.94:0.3"
msgid "94. Adantaaguttasutta "
msgstr "94. Untamed, Unguarded "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.70, sc1
msgctxt "sn35.94:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.94:1.2"
msgid "“Chayime, bhikkhave, phassāyatanā adantā aguttā arakkhitā asaṃvutā dukkhādhivāhā honti. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, these six fields of contact bring suffering when they’re untamed, unguarded, unprotected, and unrestrained. "

msgctxt "sn35.94:1.3"
msgid "Katame cha? "
msgstr "What six? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.94:1.4"
msgid "Cakkhu, bhikkhave, phassāyatanaṃ adantaṃ aguttaṃ arakkhitaṃ asaṃvutaṃ dukkhādhivāhaṃ hoti … pe … "
msgstr "The field of eye contact brings suffering when it’s untamed, unguarded, unprotected, and unrestrained. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.94:1.5"
msgid "jivhā, bhikkhave, phassāyatanaṃ adantaṃ aguttaṃ arakkhitaṃ asaṃvutaṃ dukkhādhivāhaṃ hoti … pe … "
msgstr "The field of ear contact … nose contact … tongue contact … body contact … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.94:1.6"
msgid "mano, bhikkhave, phassāyatanaṃ adantaṃ aguttaṃ arakkhitaṃ asaṃvutaṃ dukkhādhivāhaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "The field of mind contact brings suffering when it’s untamed, unguarded, unprotected, and unrestrained. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.94:1.7"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cha phassāyatanā adantā aguttā arakkhitā asaṃvutā dukkhādhivāhā honti”. "
msgstr "These six fields of contact bring suffering when they’re untamed, unguarded, unprotected, and unrestrained. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn35.94:2.1"
msgid "Chayime, bhikkhave, phassāyatanā sudantā suguttā surakkhitā susaṃvutā sukhādhivāhā honti. "
msgstr "These six fields of contact bring happiness when they’re well tamed, well guarded, well protected, and well restrained. "

msgctxt "sn35.94:2.2"
msgid "Katame cha? "
msgstr "What six? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.94:2.3"
msgid "Cakkhu, bhikkhave, phassāyatanaṃ sudantaṃ suguttaṃ surakkhitaṃ susaṃvutaṃ sukhādhivāhaṃ hoti … pe … "
msgstr "The field of eye contact brings happiness when it’s well tamed, well guarded, well protected, and well restrained. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.94:2.4"
msgid "jivhā, bhikkhave, phassāyatanaṃ sudantaṃ suguttaṃ surakkhitaṃ susaṃvutaṃ sukhādhivāhaṃ hoti … pe … "
msgstr "The field of ear contact … nose contact … tongue contact … body contact … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.94:2.5"
msgid "mano, bhikkhave, phassāyatanaṃ sudantaṃ suguttaṃ surakkhitaṃ susaṃvutaṃ sukhādhivāhaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "The field of mind contact brings happiness when it’s well tamed, well guarded, well protected, and well restrained. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.94:2.6"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cha phassāyatanā sudantā suguttā surakkhitā susaṃvutā sukhādhivāhā hontī”ti. "
msgstr "These six fields of contact bring happiness when they’re well tamed, well guarded, well protected, and well restrained.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.94:2.7"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā … pe … "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "sn35.94:2.8"
msgid "etadavoca satthā: "
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc3
#. VAR: Saḷeva → chaḷeva (bj, s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn35.94:3.1"
msgid "“Saḷeva phassāyatanāni bhikkhavo, "
msgstr "“Mendicants, it’s just the six fields of contact "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:3.2"
msgid "Asaṃvuto yattha dukkhaṃ nigacchati; "
msgstr "that lead the unrestrained to suffering. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:3.3"
msgid "Tesañca ye saṃvaraṇaṃ avedisuṃ, "
msgstr "Those who understand how to restrain them "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:3.4"
msgid "Saddhādutiyā viharantānavassutā. "
msgstr "live with faith as partner, uncorrupted. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn35.94:4.1"
msgid "Disvāna rūpāni manoramāni, "
msgstr "When you’ve seen pleasant sights "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:4.2"
msgid "Athopi disvāna amanoramāni; "
msgstr "and unpleasant ones, too, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:4.3"
msgid "Manorame rāgapathaṃ vinodaye, "
msgstr "get rid of desire for the pleasant, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:4.4"
msgid "Na cāppiyaṃ meti manaṃ padosaye. "
msgstr "without hating what you don’t like. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.71, sc5
msgctxt "sn35.94:5.1"
msgid "Saddañca sutvā dubhayaṃ piyāppiyaṃ, "
msgstr "When you’ve heard sounds both liked and disliked, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:5.2"
msgid "Piyamhi sadde na samucchito siyā; "
msgstr "don’t fall under the thrall of sounds you like, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:5.3"
msgid "Athoppiye dosagataṃ vinodaye, "
msgstr "get rid of hate for the unliked, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:5.4"
msgid "Na cāppiyaṃ meti manaṃ padosaye. "
msgstr "and don’t hurt your mind by thinking of what you don’t like. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn35.94:6.1"
msgid "Gandhañca ghatvā surabhiṃ manoramaṃ, "
msgstr "When you’ve smelled a pleasant, fragrant scent, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:6.2"
msgid "Athopi ghatvā asuciṃ akantiyaṃ; "
msgstr "and one that’s foul and unpleasant, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:6.3"
msgid "Akantiyasmiṃ paṭighaṃ vinodaye, "
msgstr "get rid of aversion for the unpleasant, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:6.4"
msgid "Chandānunīto na ca kantiye siyā. "
msgstr "while not yielding to desire for the pleasant. "

# NOTE: Following PTS reading: … bhotva saditan ca sadun ca
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn35.94:7.1"
msgid "Rasañca bhotvāna asāditañca sāduṃ, "
msgstr "When you’ve enjoyed a sweet, delicious taste, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:7.2"
msgid "Athopi bhotvāna asādumekadā; "
msgstr "and sometimes those that are bitter, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:7.3"
msgid "Sāduṃ rasaṃ nājjhosāya bhuñje, "
msgstr "don’t be attached to enjoying sweet tastes, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:7.4"
msgid "Virodhamāsādusu nopadaṃsaye. "
msgstr "and don’t despise the bitter. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
#. VAR: majje → majjhe (si, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn35.94:8.1"
msgid "Phassena phuṭṭho na sukhena majje, "
msgstr "Don’t be intoxicated by a pleasant touch, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:8.2"
msgid "Dukkhena phuṭṭhopi na sampavedhe; "
msgstr "and don’t tremble at a painful touch. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:8.3"
msgid "Phassadvayaṃ sukhadukkhe upekkhe, "
msgstr "Look with equanimity at the duality of pleasant and painful contacts, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:8.4"
msgid "Anānuruddho aviruddha kenaci. "
msgstr "without favoring or opposing anything. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn35.94:9.1"
msgid "Papañcasaññā itarītarā narā, "
msgstr "People generally let their perceptions proliferate; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:9.2"
msgid "Papañcayantā upayanti saññino; "
msgstr "perceiving and proliferating, they are attracted. "

# NOTE: For manomaya here, compare thag 21.1, which has Sabbaso gehasitañca vitakkaṃ;
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:9.3"
msgid "Manomayaṃ gehasitañca sabbaṃ, "
msgstr "When you’ve dispelled all thoughts of the lay life, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:9.4"
msgid "Panujja nekkhammasitaṃ irīyati. "
msgstr "wander intent on renunciation. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "sn35.94:10.1"
msgid "Evaṃ mano chassu yadā subhāvito, "
msgstr "When the mind is well developed like this regarding the six, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:10.2"
msgid "Phuṭṭhassa cittaṃ na vikampate kvaci; "
msgstr "it doesn’t waver at contacts at all. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.94:10.3"
msgid "Te rāgadose abhibhuyya bhikkhavo, "
msgstr "Mendicants, those who have mastered greed and hate "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Bhavattha → bhavātha (bj) | bhavatha (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn35.94:10.4"
msgid "Bhavattha jātimaraṇassa pāragā”ti. "
msgstr "go beyond birth and death.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.94:10.5"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

